A stack works by maintaining a stack frame for each element in the stack, and this frame contains the data element and a link to the superframe (i.e., the frame that contains the element above it in the stack). The process of pushing an element onto the stack involves creating a new frame for the element, and linking it to the superframe. Similarly, the process of popping an element from the stack involves following the link from the top frame to the element, and then removing it from the stack.

